Bonial.com (part of Axelspringer) / Sr. Android Developer/ Full time/ Hybrid (3 days per month at the office is a must) / Visa sponsorship / Berlin

Bonial is part of Axel Springer SE and is the lead “Drive to Store” partner in Germany and France. We inspire millions of users every day by connecting them to their favorite retailers and brands through kaufDA and MeinProspekt in Germany, and Bonial in France. 
We have an open position: "Senior Android Developer" and as an Android Engineer in our Mobile development team you make significant contributions to the development of the Bonial Products in Germany and France for Android smartphones and tablets.

You will have the opportunity to:
Give a significant contribution to our Apps (KaufDA, MeinProspekt, and Bonial) and Business;
Work in an agile environment while dealing with complexity and trying out new technologies;
Have your own impact in a cross-functional set-up to help shape our products;
Explore other state-of-the-art technologies like AWS, Firebase, Bitrise, SonarCloud & SauceLabs;

Requirements: 
At least 5 years of practical experience in Android Development with a focus on Kotlin;
Experiences in Kotlin & Java (we use Kotlin)
First-hand experience with Kotlin coroutines and Jetpack Compose;
Familiarity with web technologies and web services (such as HTTPS, JSON, REST); 
Strong analytical, modeling, and architectural skills; 
Experience working in distributed and cross-functional teams while applying modern software development practices such as continuous integration, code reviews, and pair programming; 
Interest or first-hand experience in mentoring junior developers; 
Fluent communication skills in English; German is NOT required!

Contact: Send your CV to Atefeh.heydari@bonial.com
